Panicum sumatrense

   [8286.jpg]
    Authority   Roth. ex Roem & Schult.
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms   Panicum miliare auct. non Lam.
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 8286

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A grass with erect or geniculate culms reaching
   30-100 cm in height. Leaf-blades linear. USES The straw is used as
   fodder. The grain is cooked as rice or sometimes ground into flour and
   made into bread. GROWING PERIOD Annual grass, that may mature in 75-150
   days. COMMON NAMES Little millet, Sava, Kutki. FURTHER INF Scientific
   synonym: P. miliare. In India, little millet can be grown up to 2100 m
   in elevation. It is tolerant of both drought and waterlogging. Grain
   yields are usually between 225-560 kg/ha but in a good season yields
   may be up to 900 kg/ha.

   Sources
   [10]Grassland Index
   Purseglove J 1972 pp 201-202 [FER, USE]
   Duke J 1975 pp 95 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Skerman P 1990 pp 546 [FER, RAIN]
   Landon J 1984 pp 300 [FER, USE]

